The dam sends water down
the mountain in a long tight.

22
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:13,000
The water arrives so quick
that it turns the turbine upon arrival.

23
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,790
And since the river always brings water.

24
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:19,880
That's why we say it's a renewable energy.

25
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,430
For the rest, they use
heat from the ground.

26
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:25,550
It's called geothermal energy.

27
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,830
Deep down, the ground is warm.

28
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,480
As a result, they send the water deep.

29
00:01:30,646 --> 00:01:35,910
It heats naturally and comes up very
hot, sometimes in steam.

30
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:40,390
This water, naturally heated
by our planet, becomes steam.

31
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:46,200
